commitResults.messageBody: Add a few user stories and a use case to the DG.

While it is more desirable to call it a Class, naming it so will
cause confusion with Java's original class keyword.

Let's name it ModuleClass to avoid the confusion, and only use
"Class" in outputs that the user is able to see.

commitResults.messageBody:
The deletec command does not unassign students from the class
when it is deleted.
This may cause problems later where there are classes that does
not exist in TA Assist being assigned to students.

Let's change the implementation of deletec command so that it
unassigns students from the classes that will be deleted.

commitResults.messageBody:
Two AddcCommand should be equal if and only if the module class names are
the same. The sessions for the specified module classes should not be
compared against each other during the equality check because it does
not make sense to compare sessions of module classes that are not yet
created (they are created via the addc command). It also further
complicates testing.

Let's use ModuleClass#isSameModuleClass instead of ModuleClass#equals to
perform the equality check.
